div.h1: Linker Script Section Layout: VMA vs LMA

text.tspan: (Where bootloader writes the binary on disk / in RAM)
[Must be within first 8192 bytes of image]
Bootloader loads zeros? NO must zero manually.
CPU sees whatever was in RAM before boot.
Used by Milestone 3 PMM to know
(far jump in stage-2 protected mode entry)
Values ARE correct at boot no zero-init needed.
(binary image has no zeros for BSS)
Whatever junk is in RAM at those

div.p: ld ENTRY(kernel_entry) /* Symbol bootloader far-jumps to / SECTIONS { . = 0x100000; / VMA start = LMA start (Milestone 1: no split) */ .text ALIGN(4096) : { (.multiboot) / Multiboot header: must be in first 8192 bytes */ (.text) (.text.) } .rodata ALIGN(4096) : { / 4KB align future: mark execute-never */ (.rodata) (.rodata.) } .data ALIGN(4096) : { / Initialized globals present in binary image */ (.data) (.data.) } .bss ALIGN(4096) : { __bss_start = .; / C: extern uintptr_t __bss_start; */ *(.bss) (.bss.) (COMMON) / Tentative definitions (uninitialized globals) / __bss_end = .; / C: extern uintptr_t __bss_end; / } __kernel_end = .; / PMM uses this in Milestone 3 / } / Milestone 3 higher-half variant adds: / / . = 0xC0000000 + 0x100000; (VMA = 0xC0100000) / / .text : AT(ADDR(.text) - 0xC0000000) { ... } (LMA = 0x100000) */
